Since $\overline{PA}$ is half a diagonal of the top face, we have $PA = 8\sqrt{2}$ cm.  From right triangle $PAQ$, we have $PQ = \sqrt{PA^2 + AQ^2} = \sqrt{128+16} = \boxed{12}$ cm.

We add the edges of the pyramid to our diagram below.

[asy]
import three;
triple A,B,C,D,EE,F,G,H;
A = (0,0,0);
B = (5,0,0);
C = (5,6,0);
D= (0,6,0);
EE = (0,0,4);
F = B+EE;
G = C + EE;
H = D + EE;
draw(B--C--D);
draw(B--A--D,dashed);
draw(EE--F--G--H--EE);
draw(B--H--A--EE,dashed);
draw(A--C,dashed);
draw(B--F);
draw(C--G);
draw(D--H--C);
label("$A$",A,SSW);
label("$B$",B,W);
